---
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Topnav from "../../components/Topnav.astro";
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

// `/agents` — the dedicated analytical-agent-memory front door
// (GLOBAL-036, agent-memory-pivot WS-07). A new route on nlqdb.com,
// not a new domain. This page is allowed to lead with the agent-memory
// story even though the sitewide lead strings (Hero.astro, README,
// llms.txt) stay gated to WS-13.
//
// Run 1 (this file) = skeleton + hero + AEO direct-answer. The WS-06
// capability matrix + typed-plan-trust-boundary moat + FSL band land in
// run 2; the waitlist CTA + demand-signal event (GLOBAL-024) land in run 3.
---

<Base
  title="Analytical memory for AI agents — nlqdb"
  description="Memory your AI agent can query. nlqdb gives an agent a real Postgres database as memory — so it can GROUP BY, JOIN, and aggregate over what it remembered, not just recall the top-k similar rows a vector store returns."
  canonical="/agents"
>
  <div class="page">
    <Topnav />

    <main class="agents">
      <header class="agents__head">
        <p class="agents__kicker">For AI agents</p>
        <h1 class="agents__title">Memory your agent can query.</h1>
        <p class="agents__lede">
          Give your AI agent a real database as its memory &mdash; created from
          a goal, not a schema. It writes typed rows as it learns, and later
          runs actual SQL over them: counts, top-N, averages per group.
        </p>
        <p class="agents__sub">
          A vector store returns the <em>k</em> most similar chunks. It can
          recall, but it can&rsquo;t answer &ldquo;how many times did this user
          ask about pricing this month?&rdquo; &mdash; that&rsquo;s a
          <code>GROUP BY</code>, and a similarity index has no query planner.
          nlqdb does, because the memory <em>is</em> a database.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="agents__answer" aria-label="Direct answer">
        <p>
          <strong>What is analytical agent memory?</strong> A real, queryable
          database an agent uses to remember &mdash; typed rows it can
          <code>GROUP BY</code>, <code>JOIN</code>, and aggregate over in plain
          English, not an opaque vector blob it can only search. The agent asks
          in natural language; nlqdb compiles the question to SQL through a
          typed-plan trust boundary, runs it on Postgres, and returns rows plus
          the exact SQL it ran. Recall is table stakes &mdash; <em>analysis</em>
          over memory is the part a vector store structurally can&rsquo;t do.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="agents__split" aria-labelledby="split-title">
        <h2 class="agents__h2" id="split-title">Retrieval is not analytics.</h2>
        <div class="agents__cols">
          <div class="agents__col">
            <p class="agents__col-h">A vector store gives your agent</p>
            <ul>
              <li>top-<em>k</em> similar chunks for a query</li>
              <li>semantic recall of past text</li>
              <li>no query planner &mdash; rollups become the model doing
                arithmetic over search hits</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="agents__col agents__col--us">
            <p class="agents__col-h">nlqdb gives your agent</p>
            <ul>
              <li>the same recall <em>plus</em> real SQL over its memory</li>
              <li><code>GROUP BY</code> / <code>JOIN</code> / <code>HAVING</code>,
                top-N, per-period &mdash; run in Postgres</li>
              <li>the SQL it ran, every time &mdash; auditable, not a black box</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="agents__honest">
          Honest scope: similarity search over an <code>embedding</code> column
          (pgvector) is an opt-in slice still landing &mdash; today the wedge is
          the analytical side. nlqdb is a database, not a vector store
          (<a href="/manifesto#not-title">manifesto</a>).
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="agents__more">
        The Mem0 &middot; Zep &middot; Letta &middot; nlqdb capability matrix and
        a live demo land here next. For now, see the
        <a href="/vs">side-by-side comparisons</a>.
      </p>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .agents {
    padding: clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px) 0 clamp(48px, 6vw, 80px);
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .agents__head {
    margin-bottom: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px);
  }

  .agents__kicker {
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .agents__title {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 7vw, 72px);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 0.96;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .agents__lede {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(16px, 2vw, 19px);
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .agents__sub {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.7vw, 17px);
    max-width: 64ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agents__sub code,
  .agents__answer code,
  .agents__col code,
  .agents__honest code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .agents__answer {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(32px, 5vw, 48px);
    padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.6vw, 16px);
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agents__answer p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .agents__answer strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .agents__h2 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .agents__split {
    margin: 0 0 clamp(32px, 5vw, 48px);
  }

  .agents__cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .agents__col {
    border: 2px solid var(--border-strong);
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    padding: clamp(18px, 2.6vw, 24px);
  }

  .agents__col--us {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-hard-accent);
  }

  .agents__col-h {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .agents__col ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1em;
    display: grid;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .agents__col li {
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    font-size: clamp(14px, 1.6vw, 15px);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .agents__col--us li {
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .agents__honest {
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agents__honest a,
  .agents__more a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .agents__more {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    font-size: clamp(14px, 1.6vw, 16px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .agents__cols {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
